        <rule name="Unquestioning Bodyguard" id="1be4-6d43-6a88-c45c" hidden="false">
          <description>This model automatically passes any Glorious Intervention test. However while there is a HQ model in the same unit as the Locus, he must always issue and accept a challenge whenever possible.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Preferred Enemy (Characters)" id="0033-a462-b21b-841a" hidden="false">
          <description>This rule is often presented as Preferred Enemy (X) where X identifies a specific type of foe. If the special rule does not specify a type of foe, then everyone is a Preferred Enemy of the unit. A unit that contains at least one model with this special rule re-rolls failed To Hit and To Wound rolls of 1 if attacking its Preferred Enemy. This applies both to shooting and close combat attacks.</description>
        </rule>
        <rule name="Whirling Counterstrike" id="205e-ced8-8f5d-2356" hidden="false">
          <description>This model and any unit it has joined have the Counter-Attack special rule and gets +1 initiative if they get charged until the end of their turn.</description>
        </rule>
      </rules>
