  <sharedRules>
    <rule id="7ff9-2ca7-9017-2bf2" name="Cocooned" publicationId="f840-ed73-pubd1e1" page="98" hidden="false">
      <description>The AP value of a wound caused by this weapon is the current Strength characteristic of the model it was allocated to.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="8936-83d2-a0fc-7d64" name="Crush" publicationId="f840-ed73-pubd1e1" page="99" hidden="false">
      <description>A model equipped with a Metamorph claw has a +2 bonus to its Strength during the Fight subphase.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="5e06-11ab-8ac6-6375" name="Cult Ambush" publicationId="f840-ed73-pubd1e1" page="96" hidden="false">
      <description>Units with this special rule that Infiltrate, or that arrive from Reserve or Ongoing Reserve, can chose to roll on the Cult Ambush table instead of deploying or arriving from Reserves normally. Unless otherwise specified, ambushing units move onto the table as described for other Reserves and cannot move any further during the movement phase. Units cannot use the cult ambush special rule whilst they are embarked inside a vehicle.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="c1c1-1f74-d087-a7ae" name="Lash" publicationId="f840-ed73-pubd1e1" page="99" hidden="false">
      <description>A model equipped with a aweapon with this special rule has +3 Initiative during the Fight subphase.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="39c4-8377-613e-d833" name="Life Drain" publicationId="f840-ed73-pubd1e7564" hidden="false">
      <description>Any To Wound roll of 6 made with this weapon has the Instant Death (see BRB) USR.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="abd2-de87-26fb-c254" name="Pulverise" publicationId="f840-ed73-pubd1e1" page="99" hidden="false">
      <description>When a model with a heavy rock drill makes its close combat attacks, it can instead make a single pulverise attack. If it does so, roll To Hit as normal, but resolve the hit at S10 AP1.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="7076-ce81-4717-92db" name="Resonance" publicationId="f840-ed73-pubd1e1" page="98" hidden="false">
      <description>To Wound and Armour Penetration rolls of 6 made with a weapon with this special rule are resolved at AP1.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="68a1-1058-e764-744e" name="Return to the Shadows" publicationId="f840-ed73-pubd1e1" page="96" hidden="false">
      <description>Instead of moving in the movement phase, any unit with this special rule that is not within 6&quot; of any enemy models, can be removed from the battlefield and placed into Ongoing Reserve. A unit cannot Return to the Shadows in the same turn it arrives from Reserves or Ongoing Reserves, and cannot do so whilst embarked in a vehicle.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="7ae4-44e1-0be4-896c" name="Scythe" publicationId="f840-ed73-pubd1e1" page="99" hidden="false">
      <description>A model equipped with a Metamorph talon has a +1 bonus to Weapon Skill during the Fight subphase. A model equipped with two Metamorph talons has a +2 bonus to Weapon Skill during the Fight subphase instead.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="1219-8219-ab18-839a" name="Snip" publicationId="f840-ed73-pubd1e1" page="99" hidden="false">
      <description>When a model suffers one or more unsaved Wounds from this weapon, it must pass a seperate Toughness test for each Wound suffered or be removed from play.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule id="890d-2f13-d09f-5149" name="Unquestioning Loyalty" publicationId="f840-ed73-pubd1e1" page="96" hidden="false">
      <description>When a character in a challenge is allocated a wound, roll a dice; on a 4+, they may allocate it to a friendly model within 3&apos;&apos; instead. HQ models pass this test automatically.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Gene-Sect" id="d857-0598-85e6-e08b" hidden="false">
      <description>This unit can only ever be taken once. This model can never be your warlord. This model is set up as it was an HQ.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Lone Opp" id="744f-a322-a62d-a7f0" hidden="false">
      <description>This unit gains shrouded if it has not joined a unit.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Creeping Shadow" id="8774-2627-c51b-0ec8" hidden="false">
      <description>If this model has not joined a unit, it can never be targeted by Overwatch, the “Return Fire!” reaction or the “Stand and shoot” reaction.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Psy-Shock" id="7eb0-46a6-a969-4acb" hidden="false">
      <description>If a unit is hit by this weapon (even if not wounded), psykers in the unit must roll 3D6 and discard the lowest dice when making any Psychic Tests until the end of your next turn.</description>
    </rule>
    <rule name="Neurobane" id="e6af-16d1-6862-4bc7" hidden="false">
      <description>This weapon re-rolls failed To Wound rolls against units containing a Psyker.</description>
    </rule>
  </sharedRules>
